<item>
            <title>[FLUME-2654] Memory channel error message related to byteCapacity needs refining</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLUME-2654</link>
                <project id="12311321" key="FLUME">Flume</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Memory channel error message thrown in doCommit, when space runs out, mentions heap space as byteCapacity, but this value is not the actual heap capacity, as it goes through a set of transformations and gets divided by byteCapacitySlotSize&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So we need to refine the message a bit to reflect this, otherwise the user is mislead about the configured heap size&lt;/p&gt;</description>
